[Data on the exact identity (species) of the infected Chinese
magpies, and of the "other wild birds," are still missing.

Available information on possible autumn migration of _corvidae_ from
China to southern territories, including Australia, will be welcomed.

The current avian panzootic has acquired one of the largest
dimensions in veterinary history, already stretching from Indonesia
and eastern Asia to the Balkans, threatening to spread further. As
repeatedly indicated, there is an urgent need to intensify the close
involvement of ornithologists in the interdisciplinary research
efforts. - Mod.AS]

